main event: A civilian reported observing a bright white object in the night sky in Duluth, Minnesota on August 12, 1965.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 10 minutes,The object was described as being brighter than the brightest stars,The observer initially thought it was a satellite,Multiple sightings were reported in the area at the same time,There were no photographs or physical evidence of the sighting.
sighted object: One bright white object in the sky
witness description: A civilian observer with unknown reliability
